for liberty.  I can't summarize hundreds of years of thought in a few
paragraphs.  There is a lot of theoretical groundwork, and it helps to
look at raw data and many concrete examples.  It is, however, worth the
effort.  The libertarian argument is an extremely compelling one.

Studying libertarian arguments has changed not only the way I perceive
government, but the way I perceive individual people.  I respect their
right to self-determination and their good judgment now in a way that I
did not when I accepted statist paradigms.  I recommend trying it out
even if you're sure you won't be convinced.  These ideas are only
growing in influence, and if you read "25 Years of Reason" and decide
we're all crazy, at least you'll be able to wipe us out in a debate. 
Enjoy.

