Bryan Moss wrote:
> How do you measure Defects per LOC exactly?

Total number of defects found / total lines of source code in the project.
If you want more detail you can break the numbers down by code module, by
project phase, or however else you want to (assuming you collected the
appropriate details in your defect reports).

Measuring code quality this way makes it pretty easy to tell whether your
quality is improving, declining or staying the same.  The numbers will tend
to do strange things if you change programming languages, but since
virtually all commercial applications are written in C++ these days that
isn't as big of a problem as it might be.

