Gina this is a most complicated question.  Ignoring wind loads and
assuming a perfectly isotropic material (shear strength the same in
all planes), and assuming a constant gravitational field and a perfectly
rigid foundation, etc, (all the reasonable engineering assumptions)
the tower would look like a trumpet bell, wide at the base, growing
