reasons.  For one thing, this isn't "conecting the dots" a la the Man in the 
Moon.  The "Face," if it is a face, is a distinct, chiseled-looking 
morphology, not a mass of disconnected landforms connected by Lowellian 
sightlines.

>That, plus the fact that there have been several similar claims about alien 
