The big trick here that eludes everyone is that you _don't_ "decide" 
beforehand what is artificial and what's not.  You go there and find out, 
which can't be done until enough good researchers are free to meaningfully 
discuss the issue without being ridiculed.  Why Mars, as opposed to, say, the 
