Overall I don't see the process occuring in quite the way you seem to
be suggesting.  There are technologies which will make it harder for
third parties to track the flow of money, and these may pose challenges
for governments.  Exchanges of digitized data like music and videos may
progress to become exchanges of mental experiences, but it is hard to
predict the economic impact.

