Maybe, but all of this is predicated on an advanced species somehow being
unified.  Even on Earth, we have nations, regions, communities, and
individuals who do not go with the overall flow.  For instance, I heard a
news story yesterday (on NPR, I believe) about how the Amish (an American
religious group based mostly in Pennsylvania, USA) doubles its population
every 20 years.  That's an incredibly high rate.  Granted, the Amish are not
the cutting edge technologically, but I can imagine an advanced species
having its subgroups doing stuff like that.

